testsuite.name: com.tim.one.validator.IntegraTransferFundsCommandValidatorIntegrationSpec

testcase.name: When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as origin account, and user with 9f76bd8b6ca846d397cec03cdc66f6dd as destiny account and first is trying to transfer 0.01 to the destination account the result is: true
When we have a user with 5 as origin account, and user with 9f76bd8b6ca846d397cec03cdc66f6dd as destiny account and first is trying to transfer 0.01 to the destination account the result is: false
When we have a user with as origin account, and user with 9f76bd8b6ca846d397cec03cdc66f6dd as destiny account and first is trying to transfer 0.01 to the destination account the result is: false
When we have a user with null as origin account, and user with 9f76bd8b6ca846d397cec03cdc66f6dd as destiny account and first is trying to transfer 0.01 to the destination account the result is: false
When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as origin account, and user with 9 as destiny account and first is trying to transfer 0.01 to the destination account the result is: false
When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as origin account, and user with as destiny account and first is trying to transfer 0.01 to the destination account the result is: false
When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as origin account, and user with null as destiny account and first is trying to transfer 0.01 to the destination account the result is: false

When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as origin account, and user with 9f76bd8b6ca846d397cec03cdc66f6dd as destiny account and first is trying to transfer 0.00 to the destination account the result is: false

When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as origin account, and user with 9f76bd8b6ca846d397cec03cdc66f6dd as destiny account and first is trying to transfer -10.00 to the destination account the result is: false

When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as origin account, and user with 9f76bd8b6ca846d397cec03cdc66f6dd as destiny account and first is trying to transfer null to the destination account the result is: false

When we have a user with <script>alert('josdem')</script> as origin account, and user with 9f76bd8b6ca846d397cec03cdc66f6dd as destiny account and first is trying to transfer 0.01 to the destination account the result is: false

When we have a user with 51d172788b034b738565f7dd4d4cb2fe as origin account, and user with <script>alert('josdem')</script> as destiny account and first is trying to transfer 0.01 to the destination account the result is: false
